t: Tremble at the Presence of the Lord
When*pn Israel went out from Egypt, the*ld house of Jacob from a people of strange language,
Judah*ln became his sanctuary, Israel*ld his dominion.
The*pn sea looked and fled; Jordan*ld turned back.
The*ln mountains skipped like rams, the*ld hills like lambs.
What*pn ails you, O sea, that you flee? O*ld Jordan, that you turn back?
O*ln mountains, that you skip like rams? O*ld hills, like lambs?
Tremble,*pn O earth, at the presence of the Lord, at*ld the presence of the God of Jacob,
who*ln turns the rock into a pool of water, the*ld flint into a spring of water.
